<tr>
<td><a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Gandamak" title="Battle of Gandamak">Battle of Gandamak</a></td>
<td><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1842-01-13"><a href="/wiki/January_13" title="January 13">13 January</a> <a href="/wiki/1842" title="1842">1842</a></span></td>
<td>80 British Soldiers</td>
<td>4000+ Afghan Tribesmen</td>
<td>1:50</td>
<td>The remains of a British and East India Company army retreating through the Khyber Pass made a desperate last stand against Afghan tribesmen who had been sniping and charging them for weeks in the thick of an Afghan winter. Having dwindled from a force of around 14,000 men, the survivors, consisting mainly of officers and men from the 44th East Essex Regiment and officers of the Bengal Artillery, formed a rough square formation on the top of a rocky snow-clad hilltop near the village of Gandamack and fought to the last. Only a handful of wounded were taken prisoner.</td>
</tr>
