<tr>
<td colspan="6" style="border-top:1px solid #cee0f2;"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Gallipoli" title="Battle of Gallipoli" class="mw-redirect">Battle of Gallipoli</a></td>
<td><a href="/w/index.php?title=April-December&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="April-December (page does not exist)">April-December</a> 1915</td>
<td><a href="/w/index.php?title=Ottoman_forces&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Ottoman forces (page does not exist)">Ottoman forces</a></td>
<td>Coalition Armies</td>
<td></td>
<td>The Gallipoli campaign took place between April and December 1915 in an effort to take the Dardanelles from the Turkish Ottoman Empire (an ally of Germany and Austria) and thus force it out of the war. Some 60,000 Australians and 18,000 New Zealanders were part of a larger British force. Some 26,000 Australians and 7,571 New Zealanders were wounded; and 7,594 Australians and 2,431 New Zealanders were killed. In numerical terms, Gallipoli was a minor campaign, but it took on considerable national and personal importance to the Australians and New Zealanders who fought there. Bouvet and Irresistible are sunk together with coalition dreams to get Istanbul.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="6" style="border-top:1px solid #cee0f2;"></td>
