<tr>
<td><a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Doiran" title="Battle of Doiran">Battle of Doiran</a></td>
<td><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1918-09-18"><a href="/wiki/September_18" title="September 18">18 September</a> <a href="/wiki/1918" title="1918">1918</a></span></td>
<td>35,000 <a href="/wiki/Bulgaria" title="Bulgaria">Bulgarian</a> troops (1 Division)</td>
<td>at least 75,000 <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">British</a> and <a href="/wiki/Greece" title="Greece">Greek</a> troops (6 Divisions)</td>
<td>1:2,5-3</td>
<td>The stand of the Bulgarian 9th Infantry Division on the fortified position around Doiran under General <a href="/wiki/Vladimir_Vazov" title="Vladimir Vazov">Vladimir Vazov</a> against superior Allied forces. The Bulgarians inflicted 7,000 casualties on the enemy while losing 3,000 soldiers<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9" title=""><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup>. The Bulgarian victory saved the country from an Allied occupation.</td>
</tr>
