<tr>
<td><a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Long_Tan" title="Battle of Long Tan" class="mw-redirect">Battle of Long Tan</a></td>
<td><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="08-18"><a href="/wiki/August_18" title="August 18">18 August</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1966-08-19"><a href="/wiki/August_19" title="August 19">19 August</a> <a href="/wiki/1966" title="1966">1966</a></span></td>
<td>Australian Army (108)</td>
<td>North Vietnamese Army, Viet Cong (1,500-2,650)</td>
<td>1:15</td>
<td>The Battle of Long Tần is arguably the most famous battle fought by the Australian Army during the Vietnam War. It was fought in a rubber plantation near the village of Long Tần, about 4&#160;km north-east of Vung Tau, South Vietnam on August 18–19, 1966.</td>
</tr>
