<td><a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Khe_Sanh" title="Battle of Khe Sanh">Battle of Khe Sanh</a></td>
<td><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-21"><a href="/wiki/January_21" title="January 21">21 January</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1968-04-08"><a href="/wiki/April_8" title="April 8">8 April</a> <a href="/wiki/1968" title="1968">1968</a></span></td>
<td>6,000 Marines, 350 tactical fighter-bombers, 60 B-52s, 30 reconnaissance aircraft, 40,000 tons of bombs</td>
<td>20,000 North Vietnamese</td>
<td>roughly 1:3</td>
<td>6,000 U.S. forces, primarily Marines backed up by 350 tactical fighters and 60 B-52s, successfully defended this base against 20,000 North Vietnamese forces. Roughly 40,000 tons of bombs were dropped in around 12000 sorties.</td>
